UDA presidential candidate William Ruto on Saturday led campaigns in Kajiado and Narok counties. Ruto led rallies through Supa Nkapu in Narok before proceeding to Ntulele in Narok East constituency. His itinerary started in Namanga in Kajiado South before heading to Kitengela in Kajiado East constituency. Ruto on Friday took his campaigns to Kilifi and Mombasa counties, the last of his charm offensive in the region that largely backs Raila Odinga. He was accompanied by his running mate Rigathi Gachagua, Amani National Congress leader Musalia Mudavadi and Ford Kenya leader Moses Wetangula. Others present were, Speaker Justin Muturi, Gatundu South MP Moses Kuria, Tharaka Nithi Senator Kithure Kindiki, Katoo Ole Metito, Kiharu MP Ndindi Nyoro, Senator for Elgeyo-Marakwet  Kipchumba Murkomen among other leaders.